author: maxb
msg: Buildsystem: Do not declare mod_*_svn as having undefined symbols, since
on the only platform which cares (Cygwin), it necessary to make those symbols
defined by including extra apache libraries are added to the link command, to
have any hope of making the build work.
* build.conf (mod_dav_svn, mod_authz_svn): Remove undefined-lib-symbols = yes.

author: maxb
msg: * build/ac-macros/svn-macros.m4 (SVN_CONFIG_NICE): Prefix the reinvocation of
configure with "exec" - this makes the config.nice file itself be closed,
before configure attempts to rewrite it - this matters on Cygwin.
Also, suppress adding --no-recursion or --no-create to ./config.nice, since
config.status --recheck appends these options, which are likely not to be
wanted when config.nice is used.
